&quot;Things have settled down here.  Do you require any assistence&quot; asked
Perseus.

Meanwhile

&quot;This bores me...&quot; said Depthcharge as he paced back and forth in front of
the entrance.  &quot;I&#39;m not used to being kept indoors.&quot;

&quot;You said it pal,&quot; replied Ravenchief, who was leaning against the door,
occasionally peeking out the small windows.

&quot;How about we leave and go hunt some preds, or unicronians.  It&#39;s useless
hanging around her&quot; suggested Depthcharge, stopping his pacing for a moment.

&quot;I don&#39;t like to disobey orders,&quot; replied Ravenchief.  &quot;How about I ask to
go on a patrol?&quot;

Deptcharge nodded, then Ravenchief walked back through the command center to
Perseus&#39; office.

&quot;Excuse me Sir.&quot;

&quot;What is it Ravenchief?&quot;

&quot;Me and Depthcharge want to go take a look around Relay.&quot;

Perseus looked up from the radio controls.

&quot;That fine, just don&#39;t get in over your head.  Don&#39;t go out of your way to
be seen, and don&#39;t lead a hoard of enemies back here.  That&#39;s the last thing
we need,&quot; he lectured.  &quot;Check in with Salveo every 30 cycles.  If he
doesn&#39;t hear from you, we&#39;re going assume you ran into trouble and come
after you.&quot;

&quot;Rodger.  Uh... who&#39;s in charge?&quot;

&quot;Technically he outranks you, though we&#39;re not the same organization.
Listen to what he says, but you&#39;re in charge of reporting back to me.&quot;

&quot;I understand, we&#39;ll work together.&quot;

